chinh: a female given name from Chinese
choài: to dive, to stretch oneself to the full
chạng: Central Vietnam and Southern Vietnam form of giạng (“to spread out; split; extend (diagonally)”)
chững: to briefly halt; to miss a beat (to momentarily falter)
crush: crush (the person whom someone has an infatuation with)
cuông: North Central Vietnam form of công (“peafowl”)
khang: a male given name from Chinese
napan: napalm (a kind of flammable, viscous substance)
nghèn: a river in Hà Tĩnh Province, Vietnam
nghía: to peek; to take a peek
nhiễn: Southern Vietnam and Central Vietnam form of nhuyễn (“mashy”)
nhùng: a river in Quảng Trị Province, Vietnam, a tributary of the Vĩnh Định River
organ: keyboard (device with keys of a musical keyboard)
phảng: kind of sickle for cutting wild grass
thiệu: a male given name from Chinese
thoàn: Central Vietnam and Southern Vietnam form of thuyền (“watercraft”)
đcstq: initialism of Đảng Cộng sản Trung Quốc (“Communist Party of China”)
